    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Shock Waves From the Mideast, on Two Fronts</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by retired lieutenant commander Edward E Komzelman says attack on USS Cole should generate immediate response, and not just words</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Blast Kills Sailors on U.S. Ship in Yemen'' (front page, Oct. 13):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Blast Kills Sailors on U.S. Ship in Yemen'' (front page, Oct. 13):</p>
        <p>The attack on a United States naval vessel should generate an immediate and unmistakable response from our government. Alas, words will be the response. Scores of sailors and grieving families will have to be satisfied with words. The perpetrating government and responsible group will gloat, and America will lose the world's respect as well as those precious young lives.</p>
        <p>EDWARD E. KOMZELMAN  Escondido, Calif., Oct. 13, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a retired lieutenant commander, United States Navy.</p>
      </block>
